member.name: F:Tao.FFmpeg.FFmpeg.FF_INPUT_BUFFER_PADDING_SIZE
member.summary: Required number of additionally allocated bytes at the end of the input bitstream for decoding. this is mainly needed because some optimized bitstream readers read 32 or 64 bit at once and could read over the end Note, if the first 23 bits of the additional bytes are not 0 then damaged MPEG bitstreams could cause overread and segfault

members.member: input bitstream might be truncated at a random location instead of only at frame boundaries

member.name: F:Tao.FFmpeg.FFmpeg.CODEC_CAP_SMALL_LAST_FRAME
member.summary: * Codec can be fed a final frame with a smaller size. * This can be used to prevent truncation of the last audio samples.
